SIMPLE: insularity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insularity
<hw>In`su*lar"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>insularit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or quality of being an island or
consisting of islands; insulation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>insularity</qex> of Britain was first shown by Agricola,
who sent his fleet round it.</q> <rj><qau>Pinkerton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Narrowness or illiberality of opinion; prejudice;
exclusiveness; <as>as, the <ex>insularity</ex> of the Chinese or of the
aristocracy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insularly</ent>⟦br⟧
